1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
T cells hunt infected cells and coordinate immune responses.

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:06,000
But how do they do it?

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:11,600
T cells are a type of white blood cell crucial for your immune defense.

4
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:14,800
They recognize and destroy cells that are infected.

5
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:18,400
Imagine tiny warriors navigating your body, seeking out threats.

6
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:21,600
This is how T cells patrol your system.

7
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:28,800
Recent studies show T cells also help other immune cells function better, like a conductor in an orchestra.

8
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:33,600
So, without T cells, your body would struggle to fend off infections.

9
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,000
They are vital to your health!

10
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Curious about more immune secrets?

11
